  <object name="Street">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <description>You're now on the street.  Cars drive swerve past you and keep honking their horns for some reason. Suddenly, you hear the sound of the garbage truck. Oh how you love chasing the garbage truck! Now which direction did that sound come from?  Good thing you have powerful senses to track it down.</description>
    <exit alias="west" to="toDogPuzzle">
      <inherit name="westdirection" />
    </exit>
    <command name="sniff">
      <pattern>sniff; smell</pattern>
      <script>
        msg ("You take a whiff of the garbage truck.  It went east!")
      </script>
    </command>
    <command name="go east">
      <pattern>go east</pattern>
      <script>
        msg ("You'll have to go faster than that if you want to catch up to it.")
      </script>
    </command>
    <command>
      <pattern>run</pattern>
      <script><![CDATA[
        if (Got(chew toy)) {
          msg ("You can’t get running if you have a chew toy in your mouth. It'll slow you down and you might swallow it.")
        }
        else {
          msg ("As you near the back of the truck, you see something dangling out the back end. It looks mechanical. Might be worth catching for further investigation. And chewing of course. Plastic is always fun to chew.  But oh no, you're losing it!<br/><br/>")
        }
      ]]></script>
    </command>
    <command>
      <pattern>run faster</pattern>
      <script><![CDATA[
        msg ("As you pick up speed your tongue slips out of your mouth spraying saliva everywhere.You’re keeping pace with the garbage truck now. What you realize is a mouse is dangling an inch away from your nose. Not a real mouse of course. That thing that humans like to hold when they’re sitting in front of the lit up screen with all the buttons. <br/>")
        SetObjectFlagOn (Ford the cat, "atTruck")
      ]]></script>
    </command>
    <object name="mouse2">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look><![CDATA[It is a hard plastic mouse. It has remnants of the smell from the garbage truck ingrained in its surface. <br/>]]></look>
      <feature_usegive />
      <take />
      <scenery />
      <takemsg>Yes! You’ve got it! You stop running, your tongue lolling out from your mouth as you pant from the heat of the chase. </takemsg>
      <visible />
      <alias>mouse</alias>
      <bite type="script">
        if (GetBoolean(Ford the cat, "atTruck")) {
          msg ("Yes! You’ve got it! You stop running, your tongue lolling out from your mouth as you pant from the heat of the chase.  Then just as you are basking in your triumph from catching the computer mouse, your feline friend Ford comes around the corner. ")
          AddToInventory (mouse2)
        }
      </bite>
      <chew type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (GetBoolean(Ford the cat, "atTruck")) {
          msg ("There’s not much to give. It isn’t as enjoyable as you were hoping it would be. Nothing like your rubber bone, or a good leather shoe. It was still fun to catch though. <br/><br/>As you are basking in your triumph from catching the computer mouse, your feline friend Ford comes around the corner. ")
        }
      ]]></chew>
      <givethemouse type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("After reasoning that you don’t really need a mouse anyway, you give it to Ford. The feeling of triumph after catching it is enough for you. The thrill of the chase as they say. <br/><br/>Ford doesn’t seem all that grateful considering the generous gift you just gave him. He bounds off with the mouse hanging from his mouth. Maybe one of these days he’ll be a bit friendlier. That’s a lot to ask for from a cat though. <br/><br/>Dark.<br/><br/>You are back on the vogon ship, with the “mouse” that Dog gave you. It’s surprising how useful he has been to you lately, being a dog after all. <br/>")
        RemoveObject (mouse2)
        MoveObject (Ford the cat, Machine Room North)
      ]]></givethemouse>
      <givetoanything type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("After reasoning that you don’t really need a mouse anyway, you give it to Ford. The feeling of triumph after catching it is enough for you. The thrill of the chase as they say. <br/><br/>Ford doesn’t seem all that grateful considering the generous gift you just gave him. He bounds off with the mouse hanging from his mouth. Maybe one of these days he’ll be a bit friendlier. That’s a lot to ask for from a cat though. <br/><br/>Dark.<br/><br/>You are back on the vogon ship, with the “mouse” that Dog gave you. It’s surprising how useful he has been to you lately, being a dog after all. ")
        MoveObject (Ford the cat, Machine Room North)
      ]]></givetoanything>
      <ontake type="script">
        AddToInventory (mouse2)
        msg ("Then just as you are basking in your triumph from catching the computer mouse, your feline friend Ford comes around the corner. ")
      </ontake>
      <giveto type="scriptdictionary" />
      <givesingle type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("After reasoning that you don’t really need a mouse anyway, you give it to Ford. The feeling of triumph after catching it is enough for you. The thrill of the chase as they say. <br/><br/>Ford doesn’t seem all that grateful considering the generous gift you just gave him. He bounds off with the mouse hanging from his mouth. Maybe one of these days he’ll be a bit friendlier. That’s a lot to ask for from a cat though. <br/><br/>Dark.<br/><br/>You are back on the vogon ship, with the “mouse” that Dog gave you. It’s surprising how useful he has been to you lately, being a dog after all. ")
        MoveObject (Ford the cat, Machine Room North)
      ]]></givesingle>
      <grab type="script">
        if (GetBoolean(Ford the cat, "atTruck")) {
          msg ("Yes! You’ve got it! You stop running, your tongue lolling out from your mouth as you pant from the heat of the chase.  Then just as you are basking in your triumph from catching the computer mouse, your feline friend Ford comes around the corner. ")
          AddToInventory (mouse2)
        }
      </grab>
    </object>
    <command>
      <pattern>listen</pattern>
      <script><![CDATA[
        msg ("Yep. That is definitely the garbage truck. Its strong and delicious smell wafts towards you from the east.<br/>")
      ]]></script>
    </command>
    <object name="Ford1">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <giveto type="string"></giveto>
      <scenery />
      <attr name="go to" type="script">
        msg ("Carrying the mouse in your mouth, you go over to Ford to show him your latest prize. He doesn’t seem all that impressed in your ability to catch the mouse, but seems interested in the mouse none the less.  \"Will you let me have it?\" He purrs.")
      </attr>
      <speak type="script">
        msg ("You should probably get closer to him first.")
      </speak>
    </object>
